data.title: Good food and atmosphere!
data.text:
Food and service was exceptional!
Reservations are deffinately a must have.
A little noisy but the music softened the experience.
Slightly higher prices are worth it.
Try it you will like it!

data.title: Cozy Restaurant/Bar
data.text: Enjoyed a relaxing evening with friends on a Friday night.  The fish fry was very good.  Drinks were amazing.  Staff was very friendly.  Service was prompt.

data.title: Evening out with Friends
data.text:
Nice cozy place and great food.
Our waiter was fantastic.  He said he was the bar tender helping out waiting tables.  He was funny, tentative and got it all right.  Had a good experience and defiantly will be back.

data.title: Great service--great food
data.text:
I have been to Frankie's around 4 times and every time I have been very pleased.  I wish I had her name as I type this but the waitress we had was outstanding.  She checked on us several times and she was friendly and bubbly. 
When they have a big crowd it can get loud but then that is any where you go.  Our food came quickly and it was very tasty and of high quality.  The dinners are out of the norm in that they include a side, soup, AND salad.  If you are interested in a Friday night fish fry, it is impossible to beat Frankie's value.  For $14 you have a few fish choices (baked or fried) plus the above mentioned side, salad, and soup and of course a bread basket.  Not that I had room for seconds, but the fish is all you can eat.  I recommend Frankie's - you will not be disappointed.

data.title: Reliably Enjoyable
data.text: A nice retreat from the noisy chains, this quietly sophisticated spot with attentive service is always a welcome respite for dinner with our 28 year old son when he happens to be in the vicinity. We all find something to please our palates. Our son loved their fettuccine alfredo. My husband prefers the cedar planked salmon. I try something different every time, but it is always good. Nice enough for special occasions or guests, but comfortably relaxed enough for a night you prefer not to cook.

data.title: Nice Dinner
data.text: Kind of a kicked up version of the old Wisconsin supper club. Very good food, and not just the old supper club classics. Nice drink selection, and then, just to make sure that supper club title is for real, you'll find classic throwback drinks like a Brandy Alexander, Pink Squirrel, and a Grasshopper on the bar menu. Good service, good portions, good prices.

data.title: Great Atmosphere - Great Food
data.text: Food was excellent as always, love the atmosphere.  The only place in Janesville that you can get fine dining without the chain feel.  The cook & owner puts a lot of effort in making sure his guests are happy.  The only complaint would be that it can sometimes take a while to get your food, but we enjoy the atmosphere that it has never been a down side for us nor would deter us from going.

data.title: Not what I remembered
data.text:
It's been several months since I've last eaten at Frankie's so I was really looking forward to it.  Unfortunately I and my husband were very disappointed.  I had the chicken Oscar which is served with crab meat.  The only thing good about my meal was the green beans.  The chicken was overcooked and hard and the crab meat was awful.  They assured me it was Alaskan crab but it tasted fishy and old.  I had had the crab stuffed whitefish months ago and I had the same problem with the crab then.  My husband's ribeye was very fatty; for the price he paid it was not worth it.  

Although other tables seemed to have great service, our server was not very good.  She didn't take all our drink orders at the same time (party of 6) and then when she took the others they sat on the bar so long I was ready to get up and get them myself.

When making my reservation I mentioned we had show tickets.  The hostess gave me her suggested time she felt was adequate but I decided to make it 15 minutes prior to her suggestion.  I'm glad I did...we barely made the show on time.

I'm hoping this isn't another one of Janesville's specialty restaurants that just can't make it over time.  I've watched too many start out good and crash.  Here's to hoping they get their service and food under better control and return to their early days of great food and service.

data.title: Yup, you get a lot of food
data.text: Unfortunately, the volume of food exceeded the quality.  Lots of sauce on everything, lots of salt as well.  Otherwise, lacking in spicing.  Visually, plates were unappealing - food plopped on a plate.  I understand that this is Janesville and not Madison, but it would be lovely to have a quality restaurant in J'ville. This isn't it.  I ordered the bourbon salmon primarily because it was the least heavy handed dish on the menu.  It was cooked just fine but the sauce provided nothing to the fish.  At least the fish wasn't drowning in the sauce.  My husband's prime rib had gristle in it.  As an odd touch, there was only one dessert offering.  I'll continue to drive to Madison to pay the same price and to get a more elevated food experience....although there will be less of it on the plate.

data.title: Great for Janesville
data.text: We've been there enough times now to know we'll have a great dining experience in downtown Janesville. Having ordered a variety of dishes, they've all been well prepared and a good value for the money. Their Friday Fish Fry is not the regular fish, potato, coleslaw menu. Instead, it's a full dinner starting with soup, choices of fish and potato or rice with no french fries or coleslaw included.

data.title: Just bad
data.text: Janesville really needs a local restaurant. Frankie's was a disappointment. Everything was really salty and the steak tasted "fishy." The server was good but the bartender told us which items to avoid when we order. Totally unprofessional.

data.title: Unfortunate first  and therefore last impression
data.text:
My husband and I had high hopes for Frankie's but were really disappointed last Saturday night.  The venue is nicely decorated and cozy, the staff welcoming and efficient in most ways but our entrees were dismal to dangerous.  My husband's chateau briand ordered medium rare, was delivered as very tough and beyond well done.  My salmon was actually spoiled and should never have made it out of the kitchen, let alone onto our table.  The odor was extremely unpleasant and after we explained the problem, the wait staff still left the offensive plate on our table until we asked to have it removed.
We tried to pay for our wine, soup and salads but the maître d wouldn't allow that and hoped we would give them another try.  We would have wanted to do that except for the fact that we could still smell the bad fish as we exited the back door. Too scary to try a repeat and we are very sorry about it.

data.title: Nice Local Restaurant - quiet and sophisticated!
data.text: Try Frankie's downtown Janesville!  We are always looking for something new (and quiet) locally which can be hard to find! Don't know why Janesville restaurants are LOUD with a bar in the middle and tons of TVs - so tired of that.  Frankie's was very nice!!!  We had Crab Bisque soup, salads, fresh bread with 2 types of butters, stuffed chicken (cream cheese, sun dried tomatoes, green onions & bacon) and tilapia with crab stuffing - all were excellent!  The cheesecake is creamy and fluffy and just amazing!  Also had the Sammy Davis martini - most awesome!  Our waitress was new and made a few mistakes but it was fine with us.  Overall service was very good!  We will be back - there are a lot of items on the menu we would like to try!

data.title: Traditional Wisconsin supper club experience. great food.
data.text: Main street location, great food.  Traditional supper club experience.  Good service and friendly servers.

data.title: Disappointing Meal!
data.text: Looked forward to trying the restaurant and brought out of town guests.  Five of us in total and we were so disappointed in our meals.  Could see if just one wasn't good, but everything was terrible.  Soup was salty and side veggies were extremely salty.  The fettuccini alfredo, which I normally love was full of pepper...pepper...pepper! Couldn't even eat it and when I mentioned it to the server he never apologized or took anything off our ticket.  Two in our group ordered it and neither of us could eat it.  Also, the bartender needs to learn how to make an old fashion - way heavy on the bitters.  So disappointed in our meals, would not go back nor recommend to anyone.  Went to dinner at 7 & no one else in the place & no one came in during our 2 hrs there...should have been a sign!

data.title: Excellent meal!
data.text: My husband and I went here for a date night and it was a perfect night!  The atmosphere is upscale and romantic.  Linen tablecloths and napkins add a touch of class.  Our waiter was wonderful.  Offered suggestions but wasn't obtrusive.  The meal started with fresh bread and a delicious cheese spread and honey butter.  Soup was next.  French onion.   Also very good and I'm not a fan of French onion.  We both ordered dinos steak which was cooked perfectly and served with delicious sauce.  I recommend the twice baked potato for a side.   Be sure to try some of the martinis.  Super good!  Will definitely be back!

data.title: Great place!
data.text: We hadn't been to Frankie's Supper Club for a while, but stopped in Friday night for dinner.  We both ordered the fish fry. I ordered the cod and hubby ordered walleye. We were both very pleased. Each meal came with a nice salad with homemade dressing. There was a variety of lettuce, unfortunately, including iceberg. We could do without the iceberg, please. Still, the large salad was nice. Along with the salad, is a bread basket with crackers and a couple pathetic buns. Skip these, though the honey butter was great.  When the fish plate came it also had au gratin potatoes and some veggies (broccoli, carrots and cauliflower) lightly steamed and still a bit crunchy. Perfect. Besides the couple missteps on iceberg lettuce and pathetic buns, Frankie's offers a wonderful meal that is way more than one person can eat. The service was great, the ambience is lovely and the price is good. This place will go back on our regular list.

data.title: fabulous
data.text: my son picked this place for his 27th birthday dinner. WOW, we had an awesome meal! server todd was super. the food presentations were above expectations! thank you for a wonderful evening!

data.title: Just so so
data.text:
Tried this for the first time and not likely to return anytime soon.  Pricey, too much salt, too many sauces.  If you're looking for healthy, look elsewhere.  Chicken Cordon Bleu had an overpowering sour taste (the aged swiss cheese). Sweet potato soufflé would have been better if not spiced to taste like pie (nutmeg?). My dining companion liked the pork loin stuffed with cranberries. Menu is limited; no sandwiches. Nothing on the menu for less than $10, including the appetizers.  Most entrees were $15 - $23.  No kids menu.  
Does it drive anyone else crazy to have a server always refer to the guests as WE?  How are WE tonight?  Are WE ready to order?  Do WE need more time? Did WE save room for dessert?  I don't recall that we invited HER to dine with us!  I'm also not fond of places that feel the need to ask if it's your first visit because they need to explain the structure of the menu.

data.title: Great fish fry!!
data.text:
Very clean restaurant!!

Great food!!
Reasonable prices!
They were short staffed the night we were there!! The only problem was that it took along time to get drinks!
